Detailed Description

Holder of a network link id.

Constructor & Destructor Documentation

WFAPI::NetworkLinkID::NetworkLinkID (  ) 

Default constructor. Sets the id to TRY_DEFAULT, the proxy port to INVALID_PROXY_PORT and the proxy host to empty string.

const wf_int32 WFAPI::NetworkLinkID::ALWAYS_ASK [static]

The special NetworkLinkID that always needs to ask the user for NetworkLinkID.

const wf_uint32 WFAPI::NetworkLinkID::INVALID_PROXY_PORT [static]

When the network access point is not using a proxy, the m_proxyPort should be set to this value.

const wf_int32 WFAPI::NetworkLinkID::TRY_DEFAULT [static]

The special NetworkLinkID that tries using the system default NetworkLinkID.
